---
VERSIONING GUIDE
---

Format: MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH

  MAJOR (X.0.0) — Breaking changes, full rewrites, incompatible API changes
  MINOR (0.X.0) — New features, new endpoints, new pages (backward compatible)
  PATCH (0.0.X) — Bug fixes, small tweaks, dependency updates

Current: 2.1.0
Next expected: 2.1.1 (if bug fix) or 2.2.0 (if new feature)

---
COMMIT MESSAGE FORMAT
---

  [type] short description

Types:
  feat     — New feature
  fix      — Bug fix
  refactor — Code restructure (no new feature, no bug fix)
  docs     — Documentation only
  style    — Formatting, CSS, no logic change
  chore    — Dependencies, config, build, CI
  security — Security fixes or hardening

Examples:
  feat: add file upload support for RAG agent
  fix: streaming disconnects after 30 seconds
  refactor: extract agent routing into separate module
  docs: update README with deployment instructions
  security: add input length validation on chat endpoint
  chore: upgrade langchain to 2.0

